<aws_cognito_security_guide>
<title>AWS COGNITO SECURITY TESTING</title>

<critical>AWS Cognito provides authentication, authorization, and user management for web and mobile applications. Misconfigurations can lead to account takeover, unauthorized access, privilege escalation, and data exposure. Testing must cover user pools, identity pools, and their integration with AWS services.</critical>

<scope>
- User Pool authentication and authorization
- Identity Pool federated identities
- Custom authentication challenges
- Lambda triggers and customization
- Token handling (ID, Access, Refresh)
- App client configurations
- User attribute management
- Groups and role-based access
</scope>

<methodology>
1. Enumerate Cognito configuration: user pool ID, app client ID, identity pool ID.
2. Test user registration for self-signup abuse and attribute manipulation.
3. Examine token handling for validation gaps and privilege escalation.
4. Probe identity pool for unauthorized role assumption.
5. Test Lambda triggers for injection and bypass vulnerabilities.
</methodology>

